### Replace createBackgroundTransaction with startBackgroundTransaction and getTransaction

Source: https://github.com/newrelic/node-newrelic/blob/main/Migration Guide.md

The `newrelic.createBackgroundTransaction()` method is deprecated and replaced by `newrelic.startBackgroundTransaction()` and `newrelic.getTransaction()`. This update simplifies transaction management, especially for background tasks, and works seamlessly with asynchronous operations.

```javascript
/**
 * Deprecated method: newrelic.createBackgroundTransaction()
 */
// Example of old usage (deprecated):
// newrelic.createBackgroundTransaction('MyBackgroundJob', function() {
//   // ... background job logic ...
// });

/**
 * New method: newrelic.startBackgroundTransaction() and newrelic.getTransaction()
 */
// Example of new usage:
newrelic.startBackgroundTransaction('MyBackgroundJob', function() {
  const transaction = newrelic.getTransaction();
  // ... background job logic ...
  transaction.end(); // Ensure transaction is ended
});

// Example with asynchronous background tasks:
async function processQueueItem() {
  newrelic.startBackgroundTransaction('ProcessQueue', async function() {
    const transaction = newrelic.getTransaction();
    try {
      await processItem();
      transaction.end();
    } catch (error) {
      transaction.recordException(error);
      transaction.end();
      throw error;
    }
  });
}

```

