### Example New Relic Custom Instrumentation Rule

Source: https://github.com/newrelic/node-newrelic/blob/main/documentation/otel/otel-transformation-rules.md

This example demonstrates a custom instrumentation rule for a 'producer' type span in New Relic. It specifies required span kinds and attributes, maps a span attribute to the 'host' segment, and customizes the transaction segment name using a template.

```json
{
  "name": "Producer_1_30",
  "type": "producer",
  "matcher": {
    "required_span_kinds": ["producer"],
    "required_attribute_keys": ["messaging.system", "messaging.destination.name"]
  },
  "attributes": [
    {
      "key": "server.address",
      "target": "segment",
      "name": "host"
    }
  ],
  "segment": {
    "name": {
      "template": "MessageBroker/${messaging.system}/${messaging.operation.name}/Produce/Named/${messaging.destination.name}"
    }
  }
}
```

