### Instrumenting MySQL Queries in Node.js

Source: https://github.com/newrelic/node-newrelic/blob/main/NEWS.md

This example shows how the New Relic Node.js agent instruments MySQL queries. It highlights a fix where the agent now more robustly handles arguments passed to the `query` method, supporting both SQL strings and options objects.

```javascript
// Example of instrumented MySQL query
const mysql = require('mysql');
const connection = mysql.createConnection(/* ... */);

// Previously might have caused issues if using an options object
connection.query('SELECT * FROM users WHERE id = ?', [1], function (error, results, fields) {
  // ...
});

// Also handles queries using an options object
connection.query({ sql: 'SELECT * FROM users WHERE id = ?', values: [1] }, function (error, results, fields) {
  // ...
});
