### 404 Response Handled within Endpoint (Node.js)

Source: https://github.com/newrelic/node-newrelic/blob/main/documentation/transaction-naming-philosophy.md

This example demonstrates a scenario where a 404 status code is explicitly sent from within an endpoint handler after checking a database result. Unlike automatic 404s generated by the framework, these custom 404 responses are named according to the route that generated them (e.g., `get /users/:userId`) rather than a generic '(not found)' designation.

```javascript
const newrelic = require('newrelic');
const express = require('express');
const db = require('./lib/db');

const app = express();

app.get('/users/:userId', function(req, res, next) {
  db.findUser(req.params.userId, function(err, user) {
